[BUG-001]  ip_fragmentation.py calls non-existent API
  File:    netforge_rl/actions/network/ip_fragmentation.py
  Detail:  `validate()` calls `global_state.routing_table.has_route(...)` and
           `execute()` calls `global_state.get_host(...)` and
           `global_state.get_service_config(...)`.
           None of these attributes/methods exist on GlobalNetworkState.
           This action will raise AttributeError at runtime every time it is
           dispatched, yet it is registered under `red_operator` group 11.
  Impact:  Runtime crash for every IPFragmentationAction invocation.
  Fix:     [FIXED] Replaced with `global_state.can_route_to()` and
           `global_state.all_hosts.get()`. Fixed delta path to `hosts/{ip}/...`.

[BUG-002]  DumpLSASS returns a non-standard delta format
  File:    netforge_rl/actions/red/post_exploitation.py
  Detail:  `execute()` returns `state_deltas = {'inventory_update': DumpLSASSCommand(...)}`.
           The key `'inventory_update'` is neither a `hosts/…`, `knowledge/…`,
           `firewall/…`, nor `history/…` path, so `GlobalNetworkState.apply_delta()`
           ignores it.  The DumpLSASSCommand.execute() is never called, meaning
           stolen credentials are never written to `agent_inventory`.
           Interestingly DumpLSASSCommand does not implement IStateDeltaCommand
           (no `target_ip` property), so even if the resolver called it the type-
           check in parallel_env._apply_state_deltas would skip it (list path only).
  Impact:  LSASS credential theft silently does nothing. PassTheTicket will
           always fail because inventories are never populated.
  Fix:     [FIXED] Implemented IStateDeltaCommand for DumpLSASSCommand and passed as list.

[BUG-003]  RotateKerberos returns a non-standard delta format (same pattern)
  File:    netforge_rl/actions/blue/identity.py
  Detail:  `state_deltas = {'identity_flush': RotateKerberosCommand(...)}`.
           Same issue as BUG-002. `apply_delta` is never dispatched for the
           `identity_flush` key. The Kerberos rotation (clearing inventories,
           mutating token lists, deducting 5000 funds) never executes.
  Impact:  The most expensive Blue action ($5000) has zero effect.
  Fix:     [FIXED] Implemented IStateDeltaCommand protocol on RotateKerberosCommand.

[BUG-004]  PassTheTicket grants Root even when target has no system_tokens
  File:    netforge_rl/actions/red/post_exploitation.py
  Detail:  When `host.system_tokens` is empty the code sets `success = True`
           unconditionally, granting Root privilege without any token
           check. The variable `success` is set to True first, then overridden
           only if tokens exist. The intent appears to be the reverse: succeed
           only if a valid token is held.
  Impact:  Every host without system_tokens is freely escalated to Root,
           breaking the ZTNA model.
  Fix:     [FIXED] Inverted logic: success is True only when token matches.

[BUG-005]  OverloadPLC registered under group 20 but registry only dispatches 0-11
  File:    netforge_rl/actions/red/kinetic.py  line 5
           netforge_rl/core/registry.py         line 50
  Detail:  `OverloadPLC` is registered as `red_operator` group 20.
           `SpearPhishing` is registered as `red_operator` group 21.
           In `ActionRegistry.instantiate_action()` the fallback scalar path
           computes `action_type_id = action_int // len(target_ips) % 12`,
           capping the group_id at 0-11. These two actions can NEVER be resolved
           through the scalar dispatch path. They are reachable only via the
           array/multidiscrete path `action_data[0]`, but `NetForgeRLEnv`'s
           action space is `MultiDiscrete([32, 100])`, so `action_data[0]` is
           the action type, which IS dispatched correctly in that path.
           However the JAX vector_env maps actions 0-19 for red and 0-13 for
           blue, with no entries for groups 20 and 21. These actions are
           effectively unreachable from the JAX backend.
  Impact:  OT kinetic destruction and spear-phishing cannot be triggered from
           JAX training pipelines.

[BUG-006]  sps_baseline.py uses non-existent config key `sim2real_mode`
  File:    benchmarks/sps_baseline.py  line 43
  Detail:  Config dict passes `'sim2real_mode': 'sim'`. The
           `NetForgeRLEnv.__init__()` reads `cfg.get('docker_mode', 'sim')`.
           The key `sim2real_mode` is silently ignored. Not a crash, but the
