[BUG-007]  `action_mask` shape mismatch with action_spaces declaration
  File:    netforge_rl/environment/parallel_env.py  lines 63-83, 142-148
  Detail:  `observation_spaces` declares `action_mask` shape `(32 + 100,) = (132,)`.
           `action_mask()` also returns shape `(132,)`. However `action_spaces`
           declares `MultiDiscrete([32, 100])`, a 2-element action. The mask
           attempts to overlay a flat 132-element mask on a 2-D MultiDiscrete
           space, which are structurally incompatible. Most RL frameworks expect
           the mask to match the action space shape exactly.

